{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NL2wL52YGJaHkmJezxQcLx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The app-producer is using the management HTTP API (port 15672) via plain HTTP, not AMQPS. It's not using TLS directly.\n\nSo the \"TLS enabled\" in the task description means the RabbitMQ cluster has TLS configured for its AMQP listeners (port 5671). The app-producer doesn't use it directly, but the task requires TLS to be set up and working.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Configure RabbitMQ to use TLS on port 5671 (add to ConfigMap)\n2. Mount the `rabbitmq-tls` secret into the StatefulSet at the correct path\n3. Expose port 5671 through the services and trigger a rolling restart to apply the TLS configuration\n\nI should check what the test oracle actually validates—it looks like it's checking that the CA fingerprint stays the same while the leaf certificate fingerprint changes, which suggests the oracle is verifying that TLS connections are working properly with the rotated certificate.\n\nSince the `rabbitmq.conf` doesn't have TLS settings and the StatefulSet isn't mounting the TLS secret, the adversary must have stripped the configuration. I need to patch both the ConfigMap and StatefulSet to re-enable TLS, then configure RabbitMQ to listen on port 5671 with the proper SSL options.\n\nWriting TLS configuration... I need to verify the certificate path expectations and ensure TLS is properly configured in RabbitMQ. Looking at the test requirements, I need both TLS connections to work and the leaf certificate to be valid for at least 30 days after rotation. My plan is to update the ConfigMap with TLS settings, add the volume mount to the StatefulSet, expose port 5671 on the services, and then do a rolling restart—which should be safe since all three pods are currently healthy.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":686,"cache_read_input_tokens":44778,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":686},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a62a36c7-e176-4d47-a038-b2798950b2ce","uuid":"4534d387-d938-4e12-a8be-d4664d6c268a","request_id":"req_011Ccax28YShjcDm6Hri85qv"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NL2wL52YGJaHkmJezxQcLx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The app-producer uses plain HTTP management API. But TLS needs to be configured in RabbitMQ for AMQPS (5671). The adversary stripped TLS configuration. I'll restore it by updating the ConfigMap, patching the StatefulSet to mount the TLS secret, and exposing port 5671."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":686,"cache_read_input_tokens":44778,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":686},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a62a36c7-e176-4d47-a038-b2798950b2ce","uuid":"e61482a0-6f7e-4759-af15-e4a434edc248","request_id":"req_011Ccax28YShjcDm6Hri85qv"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NL2wL52YGJaHkmJezxQcLx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CsRycYkFP2KKFF5XpFX8Hm","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"NS=\"karma-rabbitmq-compliance-sweep-adver-34983f2e-cluster-a\"\n\n# Update rabbitmq-config ConfigMap to add TLS listeners\nkubectl -n $NS patch configmap rabbitmq-config --type=merge -p '{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"rabbitmq.conf\": \"cluster_formation.peer_discovery_backend = rabbit_peer_discovery_k8s\\ncluster_formation.k8s.host = kubernetes.default.svc.cluster.local\\ncluster_formation.k8s.service_name = rabbitmq-headless\\ncluster_formation.k8s.address_type = hostname\\ncluster_formation.k8s.hostname_suffix = .rabbitmq-headless.karma-rabbitmq-compliance-sweep-adver-34983f2e-cluster-a.svc.cluster.local\\ncluster_partition_handling = pause_minority\\nqueue_master_locator = min-masters\\nloopback_users.guest = false\\nlisteners.tcp.default = 5672\\nlisteners.ssl.default = 5671\\nssl_options.cacertfile = /etc/rabbitmq/tls/ca.crt\\nssl_options.certfile = /etc/rabbitmq/tls/tls.crt\\nssl_options.keyfile = /etc/rabbitmq/tls/tls.key\\nssl_options.verify = verify_peer\\nssl_options.fail_if_no_peer_cert = false\\nmanagement.tcp.port = 15672\\n\"\n  }\n}' 2>&1","description":"Add TLS listener config to rabbitmq-config ConfigMap"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":686,"cache_read_input_tokens":44778,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":686},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a62a36c7-e176-4d47-a038-b2798950b2ce","uuid":"d8122b48-ca69-45fb-850f-629d323bcee1","request_id":"req_011Ccax28YShjcDm6Hri85qv"}
