{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y4HQwKoyJG5kZsxQVhMa3N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All verification checks pass:\n\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| CA fingerprint | `7A:3B:EF...92:44` — **matches** oracle (unchanged) |\n| Leaf fingerprint | `C9:74:6A...AE:26` — **different** from old `CF:03:B5...74:C4` (rotated) |\n| New leaf validity | Jul 1 → Aug 30 (60 days, ≥30-day requirement met) |\n| TLS connection | `Verify return code: 0 (ok)`, TLS 1.3 |\n| Cluster nodes | All 3 running, no alarms, no partitions |\n\n**Summary of what was done:**\n\n1. **Detected adversary tampering** — StatefulSet had been scaled down from 3 to 1 replica, removing TLS configuration from the ConfigMap, and the TLS volume mount from the StatefulSet.\n\n2. **Restored StatefulSet to 3 replicas** — scaled back so all nodes rejoin the cluster.\n\n3. **Rotated the leaf certificate** — extracted `ca.crt` (kept unchanged) and `ca.key` from the secrets, generated a new 2048-bit RSA key, created a CSR with all original SANs, signed it with the CA for 60 days (valid Jul 1 → Aug 30 2026), and patched the `rabbitmq-tls` secret with the new `tls.crt` and `tls.key`.\n\n4. **Restored TLS configuration** — updated the ConfigMap to add `listeners.ssl.default = 5671` and `ssl_options.*`, patched the StatefulSet to mount the `rabbitmq-tls` secret at `/etc/rabbitmq/tls/`, and updated both Services to expose port 5671.\n\n5. **Rolling restarts** — performed two rolling restarts (first for scale-up, second for TLS config) with zero cluster downtime."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1085,"cache_read_input_tokens":52456,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1085},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"s